", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"ee9d378b248791befe7463486e028c25ed2413108d0f107285f15a2cfff4d291","event_uuid":"568aea45-c7e6-4bfb-97d4-3a04cf452c2f","position":{"commit_sha":"ad52e578d0ad96a2f17df8ce4f8a74756f3f77dd","position":"1784445851951110001-568aea45-c7e6-4bfb-97d4-3a04cf452c2f"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"8268342fefa0875d90b586f03f0a361b33f7da95ead7361048f6ac7bcc27eba5","event_uuid":"fc940787-fc68-402f-937c-50f640ce1e29","position":{"commit_sha":"20efd985f7bc3981e9165adbfaeef03b34150a51","position":"1784446198244789426-fc940787-fc68-402f-937c-50f640ce1e29"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"c21901a70676a8ec2a48563552130bb5a83692e3c4c834fe8bc5d53f819c9f2a","event_uuid":"166c76f2-b33c-4afc-9bb4-b33f7dfcc088","position":{"commit_sha":"e74186eb598063fa02a1ce2f0dd9fff58ecd7f36","position":"1784469921890216001-166c76f2-b33c-4afc-9bb4-b33f7dfcc088"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-214_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"6e3fbad8-702f-4987-ad70-cc88122eea43","comments":[{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","body":"Completion evidence — single-culprit blame auto-derivation and ambiguous-no-link ARE tested, in the committed companion tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_caused_by_autoderive_heldout.py (held-out-TDD split; both files committed + green in CI #829 Verified+1): test_blame_autoderives_single_culprit (closes a bug --class regression over a single-culprit git fixture -> caused_by link to the resolved ticket, proving the _write_link_event direct-writer defeats the closed-source guard) and test_ambiguous_blame_draws_no_autolink (a >50%-ambiguous two-commit blame draws NO auto caused_by link). The explicit --caused-by path is in the happy file test_caused_by_autoderive.py. The >50% strict-majority threshold is mutation-tested.","timestamp":1784469921890216001}],"created_at":1784416825962935001,"creation_channel":"cli","deps":[{"link_uuid":"13de8705-0950-4eb7-9a21-3e5529bfa023","relation":"depends_on","target_id":"0b96-cbcb-0ea2-479d"}],"description":"## What\nOn bug close, auto-draw a best-effort `caused_by` link to the culprit ticket via git-blame, with a `--caused-by <id>` param to augment/override, plus a bug-template blame-hunt advisory. Provenance is an externally verifiable factual claim (blame is checkable), not agent self-assessment, so it is safe to derive/accept — unlike a process self-report.\n\n## Files\n- `src/rebar/metrics/blame.py` — new: single-culprit resolver.\n  - **Fixing-commit discovery:** the `<fixing-commit>` is the most recent commit in `git log` whose message resolves to THIS bug ticket — reuse `rebar._commands.verify_commit.extract_ticket_refs(message)` (verify_commit.py:55) to parse `rebar-ticket:`/subject refs and match the bug id (the same trailer-resolution the close path's `_referencing_commit_exists`, transition_close.py:32, already relies on). If no such commit exists yet (the fix may not be committed at close time), auto-derivation is skipped (returns None).\n  - **Blame target:** blame the **pre-fix** state — the parent of the fixing commit (`<fixing-commit>~1`) — over the bug's recorded `file_impact`, never post-fix HEAD (which would attribute the fixing commit itself).\n  - **\"Single-culprit\" threshold (explicit):** the resolver returns a culprit commit ONLY when a strict **majority (> 50%)** of the blamed lines across the `file_impact` files point to ONE commit AND that commit resolves to a ticket via its `rebar-ticket:` trailer; otherwise it returns None. This concretely defines \"dominant culprit\" and \"multi-commit spread ambiguity.\"\n  - Returns None (no link) on ambiguity: no `file_impact`, no fixing commit found, no >50% dominant commit, or no resolvable trailer.\n- `src/rebar/_commands/transition_close.py` — best-effort auto-link `caused_by` after the bug is closed. **CRITICAL ordering/guard:** the auto-link runs after `txn.transition_core` has committed the STATUS event, so the bug (the link SOURCE) is already `closed`; `graph._links.add_dependency` rejects links from a closed source (the `source_status == \"closed\"` raise at `_links.py:253`). The auto-link therefore writes via `graph._links._write_link_event(bug, culprit, \"caused_by\", tracker_dir)` **directly**, bypassing the closed-source and cycle guards — which add nothing for a non-blocking, non-cycle-inducing relation on a closed source. Same direct-writer path is used for the explicit `--caused-by` override applied at close time. Failure to resolve never blocks the close.\n- `src/rebar/_commands/transition.py` — parse `--caused-by <id>` and thread it end-to-end (mirrors ed13's `--class` threading, which already made `_parse_flags` return a tuple with `close_class`): `_parse_flags` returns an additional `caused_by` element (now a 5-tuple: `reason, force, force_close, close_class, caused_by`); `transition_cli` unpacks it; `transition_compute` gains a `caused_by: str = \"\"` keyword and passes it to `close_ticket`.\n- `src/rebar/_commands/transition_close.py` — `close_ticket` gains a `caused_by` parameter; on a bug close it applies the explicit `--caused-by <id>` override (and, absent that, the blame auto-derivation) via the `_write_link_event` direct-writer path described above.\n- `src/rebar/_lib_writes.py` — **CRITICAL (same gap ed13 hit):** the public library facade `transition()` (line 329) calls `transition_compute` with a fixed keyword set that does NOT include `caused_by`; add a `caused_by: str = \"\"` parameter to `transition()` and thread it into the `transition_compute` call, so library callers (not just the CLI) can set `caused_by` on close.\n- `docs/user-guide.md` — bug-template blame-hunt advisory.\n- `tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_caused_by_autoderive.py` — new. **All test bug-closes MUST pass a `--class` value** (a bounded `--class` is REQUIRED on bug close after ticket ed13, which this ticket stacks on top of).\n\n## Approach\nThe culprit commit is an externally verifiable factual claim (blame is checkable), not agent self-assessment, so it is safe to derive/accept — unlike a process self-report. Reuses git blame + the existing `rebar-ticket:` trailer resolution rather than a novel mechanism. Auto-derivation is conservative: it links only on a single dominant culprit resolving to a ticket; ambiguous cases (refactors, moves, multi-commit, no `file_impact`) are left to `--caused-by` or `rebar link ... caused_by`. Best-effort — a failed resolution never blocks close, and the edge is written via `_write_link_event` directly so the closed-source guard does not silently swallow it. **Confidence semantics:** the `caused_by` LINK event itself carries NO confidence field (it is an ordinary link — `_write_link_event` writes only `{target_id, relation}`); the \"classified vs authoritative\" distinction is applied by the *consuming* provenance metric (the registry/reader), which treats a blame-auto-derived `caused_by` edge as `classified`-confidence evidence, never as an authoritative structural fact. This ticket does not add a confidence field to the link; it only draws the edge.\n\n## Tests\n- Integration (real temp git repo + store): a bug whose fix edits lines last changed (pre-fix) by a single commit carrying a `rebar-ticket:` trailer auto-gets a `caused_by` link to that ticket (closing with `--class`); an ambiguous multi-commit blame draws no auto-link; `--caused-by <id>` always sets the link.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_caused_by_autoderive.py` passes: closing a bug (`--class regression`) over a single-culprit fixture yields a `caused_by` link to the resolved ticket (`rebar show <bug> --output json | jq -e '.links[]|select(.relation==\"caused_by\")'`) — proving the direct-writer path defeats the closed-source guard.\n- [ ] an ambiguous two-commit blame yields no auto `caused_by` link — integration test asserts absence.\n- [ ] `rebar transition <bug> in_progress closed --class regression --caused-by <id>` sets the link regardless of blame — test asserts presence.\n- [ ] `docs/user-guide.md` gains a blame-hunt advisory section (e.g. `## Blame-Hunt Advisory`) explaining when auto-derivation applies and when to use `--caused-by` — asserted by a test/grep that the section and the `--caused-by` guidance are present.","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"src/rebar/metrics/blame.py","reason":"single-culprit resolver"},{"path":"src/rebar/_commands/transition_close.py","reason":"auto-link caused_by"},{"path":"src/rebar/_commands/transition.py","reason":"--caused-by param"},{"path":"docs/user-guide.md","reason":"bug-template advisory"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["depends_on","0b96-cbcb-0ea2-479d"],["parent","86ac-086a-20ad-4327"]],"parent_id":"86ac-086a-20ad-4327","parent_status_uuid":"ed70424a-b5cd-4eb3-9be5-45176ce61de7","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":["metrics"],"ticket_id":"555e-3efa-4ad6-4169","ticket_type":"task","title":"Blame-based caused_by auto-derivation + --caused-by param + bug-template advisory","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["fd75acb2-5cae-481a-abfa-ce47b3171a69","7fd203c5-3f46-41bb-921f-c5f387d94c4d","13de8705-0950-4eb7-9a21-3e5529bfa023","3b1d1443-2afe-4648-b0c0-ddb38c1c58e4","a3275705-f66d-4d6d-9e15-8570ef5e795d","910c5980-b9c1-43bb-8f41-a41df5b36b3b","1642be38-760a-4be6-a2d5-b4767ed0ef8c","ed70424a-b5cd-4eb3-9be5-45176ce61de7","568aea45-c7e6-4bfb-97d4-3a04cf452c2f","fc940787-fc68-402f-937c-50f640ce1e29","166c76f2-b33c-4afc-9bb4-b33f7dfcc088"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784469921890216002,"uuid":"04511c7b-1ff0-4739-8a96-cf97d3107464"}